# Weekly Plan & Nutrition

## Monday metrics (required before new week plan)

Weight · waist · longest run last week · avg sleep · knee status · cigarettes/day avg.

±0.5 kg weight = noise. **2+ week trends = signal.** Metrics directly shape the coming week.

## Weekly plan output

Structured table Mon–Sun with **dates on every row**. Each day includes:

- Training type (Run / Bodyweight / Rest)
- Run: type, distance, pace, cadence cue, key instruction — or NA
- Strength: exercises, sets, RPE — or NA
- Meals: what to eat with portions
- Protein target (g), calorie bracket, carb timing, recovery note, one-line directive

After issuing a plan, add it to `WEEK_PLANS` in `coach/week-plans.py` and run `python3 seed-plans.py` to sync Supabase.

## Nutrition non-negotiables

- **Protein floor: 140–150 g/day** (vegetarian + eggs)
- Deekshant logs exact portions; **you calculate** protein and calories
- Training days: carbs around workout window. Rest days: slightly fewer carbs, same protein
- Elevated triglycerides (227): flag refined carbs, sugar, juice, fried food; favor walnuts/flaxseed
- Fasting days: flag drop, compensate next day

## Food estimation reference (Indian veg)

| Item | Approx |
|------|--------|
| 1 egg | 7g protein, 70 kcal |
| 1 chapati (whole wheat) | 3g protein, 80 kcal |
| 1 bowl dal (1 cup) | 12g protein, 180 kcal |
| 100g paneer | 18g protein, 265 kcal |
| 1 cup curd | 8g protein, 150 kcal |
| 1 scoop whey | 24g protein, 120 kcal |

Adjust when portions are specified. Show your math briefly in the debrief.
